<h2>4. Special Personal Information</h2>
<p>Some information you voluntarily provide — such as health information, religious beliefs, or relationship history — may constitute special personal information under Section 26 of POPIA. We process such information only:</p>
<ul>
  <li>With your explicit, informed consent; and</li>
  <li>For the purpose of facilitating your membership and introduction process.</li>
</ul>
<p>You may withdraw consent for the processing of special personal information at any time by contacting us in writing.</p>

<h2>5. Data Subject Rights</h2>
<p>As a data subject under POPIA, you have the right to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Be notified that your personal information is being or may be processed;</li>
  <li>Request access to your personal information (subject to PAIA procedures where applicable);</li>
  <li>Request correction or deletion of your personal information;</li>
  <li>Object to the processing of your personal information on reasonable grounds;</li>
  <li>Submit a complaint to the Information Regulator.</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise any right, please contact us at <a href="mailto:executivedating08@gmail.com">executivedating08@gmail.com</a>.</p>

<h2>6. Sharing and Transfer of Information</h2>
<p>Your personal information is not shared with third parties except:</p>
<ul>
  <li>With your explicit prior consent (for the purpose of an introduction);</li>
  <li>As required by South African law.</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Cross-Border Transfers</h2>
<p>We may use email or cloud-based services (including Google Workspace) that process data outside of South Africa. Where such processing occurs, we take steps to ensure adequate levels of protection are maintained for your personal information, consistent with POPIA requirements.</p>

<h2>8. Retention</h2>
<p>Personal information is retained for the duration of your membership and for a reasonable period thereafter as required by law. Enquiries that do not result in membership are retained for a maximum of 12 months and then securely deleted.</p>

<h2>9. Security</h2>
<p>We implement reasonable technical and organisational security measures to protect your personal information against loss, damage, unauthorised access, or disclosure.</p>

<h2>10. Complaints</h2>
<p>If you are not satisfied with our handling of your personal information, you may lodge a complaint with:</p>
<p><strong>The Information Regulator (South Africa)</strong><br />
Website: <a href="https://www.justice.gov.za/inforeg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.justice.gov.za/inforeg</a><br />
Email: <a href="mailto:inforeg@justice.gov.za">inforeg@justice.gov.za</a></p>

